The "and" logical operator is denoted by && 

  

Here an example for a truth table for and: 

a b a && b 

false false false 

false true false 

true false false 

true true true 

  

Use == when saying a variable is equal to something in a loup 

  

The "or" operator is denoted by || 

  

Here is the truth table: 

a b a || b 

false false false 

false true true 

true false true 

true true true 

  

The "not" operator is denoted by ! 

  

The use of the not operator is to reverse the bool outcome of the expression 

  

Here is the truth table: 

a !a 

false true 

true false 
